properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 27 at 2:15PM AKST until January 29 at 3:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Juneau has issued a High Wind
Warning, which is in effect from 6 PM Tuesday to 3 AM AKST
Wednesday.

* LOCATION...Eastern Gulf Coast and Central and Southern Inner
Channels including, Sitka, Ketchikan, Hydaburg, Craig, Thorne
Bay, Point Baker, and Coffman Cove.

* WINDS...Southeast winds of 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 60 mph
expected.

* TIMING...Winds will increase rapidly Tuesday evening and peak
around midnight Tuesday night before diminishing early Wednesday
morning.

* IMPACTS...Prepare for power outages. Downed trees and power
lines are possible. Improperly moored boats and aircraft may
break loose from their tie-downs.
properties.instruction:
A high wind warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM TUESDAY TO 3 AM AKST WEDNESDAY
